      "id": "628992a8_ce7b0298",
      "file_path": "docker-compose/docker-compose.yml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "Yes, task is link to epic NCMP to support 50K CM-Handles. Thus, we have to fine tune the JVM parameters. Otherwise, Java reserves 25% of total physical memory for the heap, and the remaining proportion becomes unused. These new parameters have been tested and the result shared on the ticket number CPS-2180.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8063,
        "name": "Halil Cakal",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "halil.cakal@est.tech",
        "username": "halil.cakal"
      },
      "updated": "2024-09-23 15:55:02.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "8b81d8b5_10f6d6af",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "c22c4bf4_69a5c912",
      "file_path": "docker-compose/docker-compose.yml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "-XX:+UseG1GC\n\nImprovement Consideration: This is a good default, especially with large heap sizes. If latency is critical, we can fine-tune G1GC with more advanced options (e.g., -XX:MaxGCPauseMillis=<time>).\n\nSuggested Value: No changes unless you have specific GC performance issues. we could add -XX:MaxGCPauseMillis=200 (or whatever pause goal you desire) to optimize GC for pause times.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2024-09-24 08:27:38.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "628992a8_ce7b0298",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
